rComments: Very nice professor. Assignments are easy and grading is very fair. Take all his courses.
Amazing Prof. I enjoyed his course and would love to take more of his lectures. Real Gem at UofT

I love Chun Wei Choo! He is such a sweet and humble man. He genuinely cares about he success do students. His instructions are clear, he replies to emails quickly, and he is a fair marker. The class is organized flawlessly and ensures you learn a lot. He is a tad soft spoken so its hard to hear him at times tho, so try to sit front and centre.

Superbly humble! Often engage students and listen to students to let students learn from each other, similar to Sara Grimes and opposite of Colin Furness. Dr. Choo is extremely friendly, open to new ideas in class and outside of class. hes also very very knowledgeable. kind of wish hes my grandpa :x

Professor Choo is great. He lectures, and then engages the class with some sort of workshop pertaining to what we just learned about. He also clarifies assignments well, and the assignments relate well to the class material.

Prof. Choo is one of the best profs. His lectures are very organized and he always has time for his students. He is very helpful and explains very clearly. His professional etiquette is impressive. He is extremely diplomatic. Since he has been here a long time, he also knows the procedures very well. I would recommend all his classes.
Professor Choo is amazing!!! Top shelf prof.
